metadata.name: Sano #100
metadata.description:
Using Coronado’s algorithm as a starting point, Sano extends and embraces the notion of beauty existing in imperfection but allows for more impressionistic compositions with less structure, letting something atmospheric and understated emerge with subtle interactions that combine into dissonant chordal expressions infusing a breadth of emotion while maintaining a characteristic timbre.

Just as Coronado referenced a beat-up vintage guitar that had a patina and sound all its own, Sano refers to the vintage amp it was plugged into. A tube-amp from the 1960s with a spring reverb that when combined with single coils and hollow body of the guitar delivered screaming feedback as well as wonderfully gritty warm tones, which this algorithm attempts to echo visually.

There are 100 artist curated outputs in this short-form collection.

Keys:
S : save at current resolution
1 → 6 : save 2000x2500 → 12000x15000
(Chrome recommended for higher resolutions)

metadata.name: Awaiting Yesterday (SoC: Apr) #175
metadata.description:
Awaiting Yesterday On A Foggy Morning (SoC: Apr)

This is the memory of my childhood hometown,
mountains, trees, high sky and wet air, 
all of them are mixed in a silence and foggy morning, 
only birds fly out of woods.

This is also the third work of a larger portfolio of work 'State of Coherence' (SoC) which explores and describes the coherence of people, cultures and the objective world.

metadata.name: Mareas del Ser #38
metadata.description:
'Mareas del Ser' encapsulate the ever-changing essence of the human experience. This art collection reflects the duality between chaos and calmness that defines our lives. Much like the ocean tides, our experiences ebb and flow, bringing forth moments of turmoil and tranquility.

These artistic pieces delve into the peaks and valleys, the challenges, and the moments of peace that compose our life's journey. Through brushstrokes, lines, and shapes, they express internal struggles and the ongoing quest for balance amidst emotional storms, seeking inner calm amidst external bustle.

'Mareas del Ser' prompt reflection on how we navigate these changes, learn from adversity, and uncover stillness within chaos. Each artwork serves as a testament to human resilience, showcasing the beauty of finding stability in impermanence and discovering peace amidst constant transformation.

Features:
30 Path Variations.
11 Color Palette.
8 Types of Frames.
3 Types of Textures.

Press "S" to download the image 3000 x 4000.

Created by Fernando Cabral.  License CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

metadata.name: Until biodiversity rains #99
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork. 

In the interpretation of biological organisms, which break paradigms by doing something different, to adapt to changes and be able to survive, paths emerge to be imitated by so many, and make life flow. The development of the work is a metaphor for those paths full of ingenuity and risk, where colorful organisms in rows open trails, sliding like subtle drops, with sophisticated turns and elastic jumps.

Some alternative paths usually hide a message along the way. Literally, one could find and read phrases in relation to biodiversity and its importance. Although it is more common to ignore them, sometimes not respect them, or what is worse, forget them. Even so, in an exacerbated insistence, here, audiovisual organizations seem to be repeating themselves, “until biodiversity rains”, and variety exploits so that ecosystems finally go it alone.


Relationship between visuals and sounds:
Biological organisms of different colors follow a path. They move forward, change shape, stop, turn. Always one after the other. At certain moments, they stretch and jump and sounds emerge.

Towards the edges of the canvas, the jumps are translated into cello sounds, mainly pizzicatos. Towards the center, the piano. From the main jumps emerges a kind of melody played by a pseudo-theremin-synth, characterized by flyaway melodies with glissant.


This artwork is 100% code, made in p5.js + tone.js.

[ Click ]  -> sound ON / OFF
[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen
[ p ] -> pause / play 

Note: This artwork is an animated piece, and requires a powerful GPU for optimal real-time playback. It is important to note that it may not run properly on mobile devices, especially not high-end ones.
It is recommended to run the piece in a new window from the “open” button.

metadata.name: Primordial #55
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Brutal Infection #144
metadata.description:
Brutal Infection explores the concept of structural organisms from a dystopian vision.The use of muted colors reflects the cold and inhuman nature of the organisms, while also emphasizing the sense of evolution, emergence, and life within these structures.

The compositions are based on trigonometric functions, aligning geometric shapes into abstract forms, creating a sense of harmony and balance amidst the chaos and turmoil of the structural organisms.

The viewer is invited to examine the tiniest details, as they are the most interesting, alive, and emerging parts of the structures themselves.
___________________

Due to differences in how shaders operate in different engines, there may be slight differences between the preview image and the live-rendered output.

To obtain the live-rendered version, you can press the 's' key in live view or alternatively, you can right-click and save the preview image.

Made with p5js and glsl shaders.

Best experienced in fullscreen.

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #285
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect “fx(haish) - the Generator”
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your “fx(haish) - The AI City” based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.

metadata.name: Gentrax EP #136
metadata.description:
Gentrax EP is a generative audiovisual artwork. Each iteration produces a generative house/garage track ~3 minutes in length while drawing out accompanying artwork. Live piece is aspect ratio agnostic and scales to any window size, but an aspect of 1:1.414 is preferred and can be set with an URL parameter.

Audio controls:
1-7: Channel mutes/unmutes
a: Filter up 
z: Filter down
c: Flanger on/off
v: Reverb (cycle thru three settings)
q: Switch bassline octave&seq (cycle thru three settings)
b: Portamento on/off

Visual controls: 
p: Fast forward to final artwork
o: Save canvas

Url parameters: 
&w=800 : Set width of canvas. If aspect ratio is not defined, artwork will be in preferred aspect ratio (1.41414)
&a=1.5 : Set aspect ratio. number <1 = Wide canvas
&wl=1 : Locks canvas aspect ratio to preferred 


made with p5.js & tone.js
Using tonejs synthesis for bass plus oneshot samples from various drum machines & Alpha Juno 2
<3

CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0
